comment_data.body:
cc @jwren 

I can trigger this on the Mac (for Java code) using the the find actions dialog (next method, previous method), but not via the keyboard (the ctrl-arrow keys are bound to mac's spaces).
@devoncarew I am also able to do it in Java code using exact âŒƒâ†‘ and âŒƒâ†“ keys, but it doesn't work in Dart.

The actions are called "Next Method" and "Previous Action" . I have never used or noticed the behavior myself as the Mac overrides the keybinding with the MacOs Mission Control and other actions.

Created https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WEB-40081 to track on the JetBrains side.

@jwren I tried both  `âŒƒâ†‘` and `âŒƒâ†“` and `Navigate > Next Method / Navigate > Previous Method` and still it failed, there are absolutely no errors in my dart file and in complete flutter project, here is the screenshot of the full file.

![ezgif com-video-to-gif](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40364434/61502811-0656a700-a9f3-11e9-8307-5147fd393f3f.gif)

I reproduced this in v2019.1 of the IJ platform, with and without the Flutter plugin installed, so the issue is with the Dart Plugin (and/or the underlying IDEA platform.)

I was **not** able to reproduce it on the 2019.2 version of IJ launching from Dart plugin source, with the above Dart source.  I suspect that this was an issue in IntelliJ platform that has been resolved.  The rolled Flutter plugin version doesn't yet allow me to install the Flutter plugin in the latest launched intellij-community/ source to confirm that the action works with Flutter Dart source.

I was not able to find any resolved issue in https://youtrack.jetbrains.com. @alexander-doroshko 

This can be closed as soon someone else confirms that these actions work with IJ 2019.2
I'm not sure when the feature was implemented / broken / fixed, but I can confirm it works for me in 2019.2.
@jwren  So what's the final solution, do I need to wait for the coming update in Android studio?
Yes.  If it was a lower-risk change in the Dart or Flutter plugin we'd push out a change for all IJ platforms being used, but unfortunately it was some change in the platform itself.
Hello, everyone. I have also encountered this problem. Is there any solution?
